<br>
The days of a 30-50K HP raid mob encounter are over anyway and with that few HP's unless the mob AE death touched, that wouldnt be much of an encounter.  Most good guilds would have that mob wasted in under a minute.<br>
<br>
In summation, I think MB was situationally a stupid target for a nerf.  The effect really has limited usefullness other than impressing your friends.  All Sony had to do in order to protect the content and the skill was take the 5 or so Mobs that it completely trivialized (VS, Son, Tal, Gore, Sev, Wuoshi, and the other completely exposed and unprotected kunark/velious content) and make them immune to the attack.<br>
<br>
You didnt see much bragging about wizards MBing Trak because he was hidden away in a dungeon, 6 wizards could easily kill him, but it would have been a real pain in the ass to get to him.  <br>
<br>
The point that I am trying to make in my posts here is that one way or another all old world content is trivialized by the abilities gain in the next set of expansions.  Killing trak or gore now is insignificant when compared to that same accomplishment in the pre velious era.  Why?  Mudflation, AA's, and Lvl Cap raises.  All of these factors unbalance and trivialize previous encounters.  Sony has 3 choices in how to deal with this....<br>
<br>
A) hit every ability that nerfs this blindly with the nerf bat (seems to be the answer of choice lately)<br>
<br>
B) Ignore it (tried that, but greedy wizards made it so that they couldn't anymore)<br>
<br>
C)  Make the exploited/trivialized mobs immune/resistant to the attacks that trivialize them.  Seems a simple solution but I am sure it is marginally more difficult than A so they will not do it.<br>
<br>
Do you think that Sony envisioned tanks with 9500hp, rangers that bow crit for 2k, wizards that crit for 5-6k, FT15, or any of the other abilities we see now when they designed the kunark encounters?  I doubt it and if they did, what are they supposed to do now?  go back and retrofit trak with about 400K more HP, an upgraded AE, flurry's, rampages, and enrages?  They can't do that because if they do then they will take the encounter away from the people that is supposed to be conserved for.  All encounters become trivial over time....  give up trying to conserve them.  Yes, one day all kunark encounters will be as trivial as the magi in guk.<br>
<br>
Vaeldayanie<br>
Sorcerer <br>
Vengeance of Lost Souls<br>
